    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, absolutely. Most languages define division by zero as NaN or throw an exception/panic/halt; we should do the same rather than silently returning an incorrect answer. Ideally a hard fork will fix this in the EVM, but in the meantime Solidity should definitely add this check itself, just like it checks array bounds.\n",
